---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work with me | Research activation and narrative strategy"
  description="Editorial Intelligence services for B2B organisations: narrative audits, research activation, thought leadership architecture, event intelligence and ongoing advisory."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="work-inner">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">Work with me</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">You have the research.<br />I'll find the argument.</h1>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>I help B2B organisations turn scattered research, customer insight and market evidence into distinctive narratives, thought leadership platforms and editorial systems.</p>
          <p>Most organisations already have more insight than they realise: research reports, customer stories, webinars and events, advisory board discussions, sales feedback and market analysis.</p>
          <p>The problem is not the absence of evidence. It is that the evidence is scattered, underused and rarely connected into a sustained argument.</p>
          <p>A report gets published. A webinar is broadcast. An event produces useful conversations. Then the next campaign starts and the learning disappears into another folder, deck or Teams thread.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence builds the missing narrative layer: determining what the evidence means, what the organisation can credibly claim and how that knowledge can compound over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co" class="work-btn">Discuss a project</a>
          <a href="#services" class="work-link">Explore the services ↓</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Problem recognition -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">This work is useful when</h2>
        <ul class="work-list mb-6">
          <li>You commissioned valuable research, but it produced little beyond the original report</li>
          <li>You have customer insight but no coherent strategic narrative connecting it</li>
          <li>Your thought leadership consists of individual assets rather than a recognisable position</li>
          <li>You run webinars and events that generate valuable discussion, but the insight rarely travels beyond the original session</li>
          <li>Your content programme resets with every campaign instead of accumulating authority</li>
          <li>You are preparing to invest in more content but suspect that volume is not the real problem</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prose-note">The right engagement depends on how clearly you already understand the problem.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Services -->
      <section id="services" class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">Ways to work together</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-12">
          <p>Some organisations need to understand what they already have. Others have a particular body of research, a thought leadership opportunity or a stream of webinar and event insight ready to develop.</p>
          <p>The services below provide different entry points into the same underlying work: connecting evidence, finding the argument and building a system around it.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Flagship: Narrative audit -->
        <div class="service-flagship mb-12">
          <p class="service-eyebrow">Start here</p>
          <h3 class="service-heading">Narrative audit</h3>
          <p class="service-prop">Find out what your existing evidence actually adds up to.</p>
          <div class="prose-section mb-6">
            <p>A structured review of your research, content, customer insight and market evidence. I identify the strongest argument already present, assess what genuinely supports it and show where valuable signals are being missed.</p>
            <p>The audit is designed for organisations that know they are sitting on useful material but do not yet have a clear view of the narrative opportunity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-includes mb-6">
            <p class="service-includes-label">Includes</p>
            <ul class="work-list">
              <li>The strongest through-lines across your existing material</li>
              <li>The evidence with the greatest strategic value</li>
              <li>Gaps, contradictions and overlooked signals</li>
              <li>Existing assets worth reactivating</li>
              <li>The narrative territories you could credibly own</li>
              <li>Recommended priorities for further development</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement-outcome">Deliverable: a concise narrative audit, evidence map and opportunity brief. Fixed scope and fixed fee. Typically completed within two to three weeks.</p>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co" class="work-btn mt-6 inline-flex">Discuss a narrative audit</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Build layer -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <p class="service-section-label mb-8">Build from the evidence</p>
          <div class="service-dev-grid">

            <!-- Research activation -->
            <div class="service-dev-card">
              <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Research activation</h3>
              <p class="service-prop-sm">Your research should produce more than a report.</p>
              <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
                <p>For organisations that have commissioned original research and need it to work harder.</p>
                <p>I turn the findings into a clear strategic argument, determine which evidence matters most and design a structure through which the research can support thought leadership, editorial content, executive communications, webinars, events and future research.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="service-outputs mb-4">
                <p class="service-outputs-label">Possible outputs</p>
                <ul class="work-list-sm">
                  <li>Research narrative</li>
                  <li>Evidence hierarchy</li>
                  <li>Editorial framework</li>
                  <li>Thought leadership and content opportunities</li>
                  <li>Executive and sales applications</li>
                  <li>Future research questions</li>
                  <li>Activation roadmap</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <p class="engagement-outcome">Deliverable: a research narrative and activation system.</p>
              <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="service-inline-link">See how this works through Hidden Hours →</a>
            </div>

            <!-- Thought leadership architecture -->
            <div class="service-dev-card">
              <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Thought leadership architecture</h3>
              <p class="service-prop-sm">Turn organisational expertise into a position the market can recognise.</p>
              <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
                <p>For organisations with credible expertise, evidence and opinions but no coherent market position connecting them.</p>
                <p>I bring together research, customer experience, executive expertise and market signals to define the problem the organisation can own, its distinctive interpretation and the evidence required to sustain it.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="service-outputs mb-4">
                <p class="service-outputs-label">Possible outputs</p>
                <ul class="work-list-sm">
                  <li>Core strategic argument</li>
                  <li>Thought leadership platform</li>
                  <li>Messaging architecture</li>
                  <li>Proprietary frameworks and language</li>
                  <li>Editorial territories</li>
                  <li>Evidence structure</li>
                  <li>Development roadmap</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <p class="engagement-outcome">Deliverable: a thought leadership platform and editorial architecture.</p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Event intelligence -->
        <div class="service-specialist mb-12">
          <p class="service-section-label mb-6">A specialist application</p>
          <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Event intelligence</h3>
          <p class="service-prop-sm">Make the value of an event last longer than the event itself.</p>
          <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
            <p>Webinars, roundtables, conferences, advisory boards and customer events generate valuable insight — speaker expertise, audience questions, recurring themes, poll findings — but much of it disappears into recordings, transcripts and follow-up content that is rarely revisited.</p>
            <p>I analyse the conversations to identify emerging themes, areas of agreement and tension, useful evidence, narrative implications and signals worth tracking.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-outputs mb-4">
            <p class="service-outputs-label">Possible outputs</p>
            <ul class="work-list-sm">
              <li>Event intelligence report</li>
              <li>Theme and tension analysis</li>
              <li>Evidence and quotation bank</li>
              <li>Content and thought leadership opportunities</li>
              <li>Research implications</li>
              <li>Activation recommendations</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement-outcome mb-3">Deliverable: an event intelligence report and activation plan.</p>
          <a href="/experiments/event-intelligence" class="service-inline-link">See the event intelligence approach →</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Advisory -->
        <div class="service-advisory">
          <p class="service-section-label mb-6">Continue the work</p>
          <h3 class="service-heading-sm">Editorial Intelligence advisory</h3>
          <p class="service-prop-sm">An ongoing editorial perspective on what your evidence means and where the narrative should go next.</p>
          <div class="prose-section-sm mb-4">
            <p>For teams that need continuing strategic judgement rather than another production retainer.</p>
            <p>The advisory relationship can include reviewing new research, connecting new evidence to existing narratives, challenging content plans, identifying emerging signals and deciding when the strategic argument needs to evolve.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="service-outputs mb-4">
            <p class="service-outputs-label">Possible areas of support</p>
            <ul class="work-list-sm">
              <li>Research and evidence review</li>
              <li>Narrative maintenance</li>
              <li>Thought leadership development</li>
              <li>Content and campaign sense-checking</li>
              <li>Signal identification</li>
              <li>Event and customer insight integration</li>
              <li>AI-supported editorial workflows</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="engagement-outcome mb-4">Retainer-based, with the scope defined around the organisation's needs.</p>
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co" class="work-btn">Discuss ongoing advisory</a>
        </div>

      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Proof -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">The practice behind the services</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-10">
          <p>This work is grounded in two decades of editorial and content experience in complex B2B markets: developing research-led narratives, turning customer insight into useful evidence and connecting organisational knowledge into systems that outlast individual campaigns.</p>
          <p>The work documented across this site shows the methodology in practice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-items">
          <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="proof-item group">
            <div class="proof-item-inner">
              <p class="proof-label">Hidden Hours</p>
              <p class="proof-desc">How one research programme became a narrative platform, content series, diagnostic idea and source of continuing market intelligence.</p>
              <span class="proof-link group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Explore →</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/narratives/winning-in-small" class="proof-item group">
            <div class="proof-item-inner">
              <p class="proof-label">Winning in Small</p>
              <p class="proof-desc">How event insight, customer stories and survey evidence were synthesised into a clearer strategic argument.</p>
              <span class="proof-link group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Explore →</span>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/applications" class="proof-item group">
            <div class="proof-item-inner">
              <p class="proof-label">Applications</p>
              <p class="proof-desc">How Editorial Intelligence can be applied across research, events, customer evidence, AI workflows and content activation.</p>
              <span class="proof-link group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent)] transition-colors">Explore →</span>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Distinction -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-6">A small, senior practice</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>I am not an agency. I work on a small number of engagements at a time, which means the analysis, synthesis and strategic thinking are carried out by me rather than delegated through a larger team.</p>
          <p>The work is particularly suited to B2B organisations in fintech, SaaS, professional services and other complex markets where credibility depends on connecting evidence with genuine subject expertise.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-6">Start with the problem</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Most first conversations are straightforward: you tell me what insight, research or content you already have, and I help determine whether there is a stronger argument hiding inside it.</p>
          <p>If the work on this site resembles a problem inside your organisation, that is enough reason to get in touch.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co" class="contact-cta">
          asavin@editorialintelligence.co
          <span class="contact-cta-arrow">→</span>
        </a>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .work-inner {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  /* ── Prose ── */
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-section-sm {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .prose-section-sm p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-note {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Lists ── */
  .work-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .work-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .work-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .work-list-sm {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .work-list-sm li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .work-list-sm li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* ── Hero CTAs ── */
  .hero-ctas {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .work-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .work-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .work-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .work-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  /* ── Service labels ── */
  .service-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .service-section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* ── Flagship ── */
  .service-flagship {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .service-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .service-prop {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .service-includes { }

  .service-includes-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* ── Dev grid ── */
  .service-dev-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .service-dev-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .service-dev-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .service-heading-sm {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .service-prop-sm {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .service-outputs { }

  .service-outputs-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .service-inline-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    display: block;
    opacity: 0.8;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .service-inline-link:hover { opacity: 1; }

  /* ── Specialist ── */
  .service-specialist {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  /* ── Advisory ── */
  .service-advisory {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  /* ── Proof ── */
  .proof-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .proof-item {
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .proof-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .proof-item:hover { background: var(--color-surface-tertiary); }

  .proof-item-inner {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .proof-label {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .proof-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
  }

  .proof-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  /* ── Outcome line ── */
  .engagement-outcome {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    display: block;
  }

  .mt-6 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .mb-3 { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .mb-4 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  /* ── Contact ── */
  .contact-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .contact-cta:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent); }

  .contact-cta-arrow { transition: transform 0.2s; }
  .contact-cta:hover .contact-cta-arrow { transform: translateX(3px); }
</style>
